I have fixed the whatisfixed bug.  For info,  apparently xml beans  knows to hex escape characters for "less than" and a few other things but not for "greater than".  To do that you use smt called XMLOptions like below.

XmlOptions xmlOptions = new XmlOptions();
XmlOptionCharEscapeMap charEscapeMap = new XmlOptionCharEscapeMap();
charEscapeMap.addMapping('>', XmlOptionCharEscapeMap.HEXADECIMAL);
charEscapeMap.addMapping('<', XmlOptionCharEscapeMap.HEXADECIMAL);
xmlOptions.setSaveSubstituteCharacters(charEscapeMap);

